House Bill 5 (AS PASSED HOUSE AND SENATE)
By: Representative Campbell of the 171st
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend an Act relating to the board of commissioners of Decatur County, approved
2 March 4, 1935 (Ga. L. 1935, p. 630), as amended, particularly by an Act approved
3 May 6, 2015 (Ga. L. 2015, p. 3718), so as to change the district residency requirements for
4 candidates for the office of commissioner; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting
5 laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 An Act relating to the board of commissioners of Decatur County, approved March 4, 1935
9 (Ga. L. 1935, p. 630), as amended, particularly by an Act approved May 6, 2015
10 (Ga. L. 2015, p. 3718), is amended by revising Section 2 as follows:
11 "SECTION 2.
12 All members of the board of commissioners shall not be less than 21 years of age and shall
13 be qualified electors of Decatur County. Each of the commissioners shall have been a
14 resident of his or her respective commission district for at least 12 months prior to the date
15 of taking office. In the event that any member ceases to be a resident of his or her
