16 respective commission district during his or her term of office, a vacancy shall be created
17 and shall be filled in the manner hereinafter provided. Each of the members shall be
18 elected by the qualified voters of Decatur County residing within his or her respective
19 commission district. In all elections conducted pursuant to this Act, each candidate shall
20 designate, at the time of qualifying, the district from which he or she offers as a candidate.
21 To be elected as a member of the board, a candidate must receive the highest number of
22 votes cast for the seat he or she is seeking; and, at the same time, a candidate must receive
23 a majority of the total votes cast for the election of a commissioner to that seat. In the
24 event no candidate for a particular seat receives a majority of the votes for the seat he or
25 she is seeking, a run-off election shall be conducted for that particular seat. All members
26 shall be nominated and elected in accordance with the provisions of Chapter 2 of Title 21
27 of the O.C.G.A., the 'Georgia Election Code,' as now or hereafter amended."
28 SECTION 2.
29 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
